                     /note="Bacteriophage lambda phage attachment site (attP,
                     P-O-P'), the Int/IHF recombination substrate carrying the P
                     and P' arms flanking the 15 bp common core. Identified as
                     attP (NOT bacterial attB) — its source AY048716.1 is a CRIM
                     integration plasmid (which carries attP), and it shares 192
                     bp of the P/P' arm region with the genomic lambda attP (a
                     true attB would share only the ~15 bp core). Detailed
                     sub-feature annotation (Int arm/core sites, IHF H/H1/H2,
                     Xis) and functional_claims pending a re-run under the
                     corrected attP identity."
